This paper is about a new approach for off-policy prediction in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a new method called Importance Resampling (IR) and compares it to existing methods such as Importance Sampling (IS) and V-trace. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also includes experiments with image data, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a likely category. Finally, since the paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is often used in control systems, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category.
